\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 Failure Playbooks\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Playbook 1: Unhappy Client
\f1\b0  Signs: Negative reply, "this isn't what I expected", vague dissatisfaction. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 1: "Thank you for being direct \'97 can you tell me specifically what fell short?" 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 2: Categorize: scope misalignment? Quality issue? Expectation mismatch? 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 3: If quality issue: redo the affected section. No charge. No argument. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 4: If scope misalignment: "Based on our SOW, [X] was included. [Y] would be additional scope. Let me offer [compromise]." 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 5: If unresolvable: refund partial or full (judgment call). Preserve the relationship and future referral potential. No project is worth a public bad review.\

\f0\b Playbook 2: Late Delivery
\f1\b0  
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Day of (as soon as you know you'll be late): "Quick heads up \'97 I need [X more days] to deliver this properly. I'd rather give you something great on [new date] than something rushed today. Does that work?" 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Offer: deliver a partial preview or interim update to maintain trust. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  NEVER: just go silent and miss the deadline.\

\f0\b Playbook 3: Nightmare Client (constant changes, no boundaries)
\f1\b0  
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Warning sign: >3 revision requests, scope creep attempts, Sunday messages expecting Monday response. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 1: Explicit conversation: "I want to make sure we're aligned on how we work together. Our agreement covers [X revisions]. I'm happy to do additional work at [$Y/hr]." 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 2: If behavior continues: "I don't think I'm the right fit for what you need. I'll complete the current deliverable and we can close the engagement." 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Step 3: Do not accept referrals from this client. Do not offer extension.\

\f0\b Playbook 4: Cold Pipeline (no replies, no interest)
\f1\b0  
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  If Week 3 metrics are: <5% reply rate OR 0 positive replies after 100 emails: 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Stop sending. Audit one of: copy (subject line CTR?), ICP (are these actually our buyers?), offer (is $400 too high friction?), deliverability (check spam rates). 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Fix ONE variable at a time. Re-test with 20-email batch. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  While fixing: accelerate warm outreach. Post LinkedIn content. Post sample teardown in 2 communities.\

\f0\b Playbook 5: Bad Discovery Call
\f1\b0  
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  Signs: prospect can't articulate the problem, "I was just curious", no budget, no timeline. 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  During the call: "I want to be honest \'97 based on what you've shared, I'm not sure I'm the right fit right now. [Explain why]. When [X condition] is true, reach out \'97 I'd love to work with you then." 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  After the call: Mark as "Not Qualified" in HubSpot with reason. This preserves the relationship and frees your time.\
